  "body": "### Description\n\nWhen we currently save `application.properties`, it doesn't trigger dev mode reload. We need to trigger reload in another way (HTTP request, manually, pom.xml save, etc.). Also, saving the config in DevUI does trigger live reload.\r\n\r\nI wonder if we could add a config property like `quarkus.devmode.trigger` that could extend which files would be watched for save triggers. Values, for instance, `config`, `*.java`, `*Test.java`.\r\n\r\nThis is open for community feedback. Please comment on this issue.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
